  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "It is essential that voters are sufficiently informed, so that the electoral results truly reflect voters' preferences.",
    "A well-functioning democracy should therefore strive to enhance core voter knowledge and to fulfill what Goldman coins the CVK criterion-\"criterion of conduciveness to core voter knowledge\" (Goldman 2002, p. 330).",
    "Relevant institutions, actors, and practices, should work towards helping voters make an informed choice and eliminate practices that undermine knowledge.",
    "For example, the private financing of political campaigns or the inadequate training of the press can undermine CVK, according to Goldman.",
    "Portraying elections as a 'horse race-like' game also distorts the proper acquisition of knowledge, as it shifts the focus from finding the best candidate to choosing a good-enough-candidate-who-has-a-chance-of-winning."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "A well-functioning democracy should therefore strive to enhance core voter knowledge and to fulfill what Goldman coins the CVK criterion-\"criterion of conduciveness to core voter knowledge\" (Goldman 2002, p. 330)."
  ]
